Danny Jan SEKOH, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Linda Stricklen SEKOH; Shannon Poore, Defendants-Appellees. No. 10-1941. United States Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. Submitted: Oct. 14, 2010. Decided: Oct. 20, 2010. *894Danny Jan Sekoh, Appellant Pro Se. Before MOTZ, KING, and DAVIS, Circuit Judges.

Affirmed by unpublished PER CURIAM opinion.

Unpublished opinions are not binding precedent in this circuit.

PER CURIAM:

Danny Jan Sekoh appeals the district court’s order dismissing his civil complaint for lack of subject matter jurisdiction. We have reviewed the record and find no reversible error. Accordingly, we affirm for the reasons stated by the district court. See Sekoh v. Sekoh, No. 5:10-cv-00251-D (E.D.N.C. July 26, 2010). We dispense with oral argument because the facts and legal contentions are adequately presented in the materials before the court and argument would not aid the decisional process.

AFFIRMED.
